<h1>About Ecology </h1>
<font face="monospace" size="5"><p>Ecology is the study of how living things interact with their environment. It includes the study of how different species interact with each other and how these interactions impact ecosystems. Ecology is a branch of biology that is concerned with the abundance and distribution of organisms. It seeks to understand how the Earth can support all life and includes the study of how humans interact with other living things and how they affect us. <br><br>

Ecology has several branches including population ecology, community ecology, ecosystem ecology, aquatic ecology, terrestrial ecology, behavioral ecology, landscape ecology, restoration ecology, and more, each focusing on different aspects of how organisms interact with their environment at various scales. </font>

